n><hr size=1> I play on Quellious, not a PvP server.  I have a Shadow Knight friend, cleric friend, and druid friend.  Any advice in destroying them in duels would be helpful =D <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umindwarpan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mindwarpan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/30/01 12:09:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=18.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> RE:</span><hr size=1> well it matters what level u are, but in general:<br>
<br>
SK: ShadowStep/Yonder and blast from afar. Keep whatever skin you have memmed and recast it if u get beat on, because most SK's watch for you to get to about 1/2 health and then BAM, they hit you with HT and your dead. In general Fire nukes work best against SK's.<br>
<br>
Druid: Beef up your FR and MR. If they DoT or Snare, run them OOM by dispelling yourself. If they DD, return the volley with some of your own. If they try to heal, stun them and then throw on a DD.<br>
<br>
Cleric: Throw on the most MR gear you have. Your hardest match. You may not win, but instead end up with both of you OOM and you running from the melee'ing cleric <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . Best bet to try to kill is BIG DD's or rains if you catch them in a long cast. If you go with medium damage quick-cast DD's, you will probably lose. Clerics can usually outheal anything you do. You have to take them to just about the point where they want to heal, and throw on a big nuke. Their nukes wont be much of a factor if you have decent MR, and you should be easily able to cast yours in the time it takes them to cast theirs. A rather cheap tactic in my book vs clerics is to get some golem wands from Cazic Thule (the zone, not the god :-) to dispell all of their massive HP buffs. Cheap, but it works. Just remember not to be stupid and go OOM casting on them if they cast divine aura. But in all likelyhood, its very hard for a wizard to kill a cleric in a prepared duel, especially as levels increase.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umaultar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maultar</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.home.net/ccyre/sliderball.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/18/01 5:06:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=18.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: RE:</span><hr size=1> Ah, Golem wands you say.  I have slain the clay golem many times are you perhaps talking of the one that spawns in the green pool area?  Thought that wand was a mage quest thingy. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uacillatemzoso.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Acillatem Zoso</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/18/01 7:52:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=18.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: RE:</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showMessage?topicID=13.topic">pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showMessage?topicID=13.topic</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
